-- AIG says obliged to consider joining lawsuit against government
-- 
-- Tue Jan 8, 2013 6:01pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/01/08/us-aig-lawsuit-response-idUSBRE90715Q20130108

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - AIG has an obligation to consider a demand by its former chief executive that the company join a lawsuit challenging some of the terms of the insurer's 2008 government rescue, AIG said on Tuesday. 
 In a statement, American International Group said its board expected to make a decision "in the next several weeks." (Reporting by  Ben Berkowitz ; Editing by Phil Berlowitz)